    "# ResonanceOS Deep Architecture Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the complete ResonanceOS architecture with progressive complexity tiers, mathematical foundations, and practical implementations.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "ResonanceOS is an advanced AI system that learns stylistic resonance from writers and generates original content with real-time tonal alignment. The system uses a sophisticated 9-layer architecture to ensure high-quality, stylistically consistent content generation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. System Architecture Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "The ResonanceOS architecture consists of 9 core layers:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Input Corpus → Resonance Profiler → Style Vector Encoder → Adaptive Generator \n",
    "→ Resonance Feedback Controller → Drift Detector → Reinforcement Optimizer \n",
    "→ Output Article + Resonance Score\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import necessary libraries\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from typing import List, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n",
    "import json\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up plotting\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"husl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"ResonanceOS Architecture initialized\")\n",
    "print(f\"NumPy version: {np.__version__}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Matplotlib version: {plt.matplotlib.__version__}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Mathematical Foundations\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.1 Resonance Vector Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "The Resonance Vector R is a 10-dimensional vector capturing stylistic features:\n",
    "\n",
    "$R = [r_1, r_2, ..., r_{10}]$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where each dimension represents:\n",
    "- $r_1$: Lexical Density\n",
    "- $r_2$: Emotional Valence\n",
    "- $r_3$: Cadence Variability\n",
    "- $r_4$: Sentence Entropy\n",
    "- $r_5$: Metaphor Frequency\n",
    "- $r_6$: Abstraction Level\n",
    "- $r_7$: Assertiveness Score\n",
    "- $r_8$: Rhythm Signature\n",
    "- $r_9$: Narrative Intensity Curve\n",
    "- $r_{10}$: Cognitive Load Index"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define resonance dimensions\n",
    "RESONANCE_DIMENSIONS = [\n",
    "    \"lexical_density\",\n",
    "    \"emotional_valence\", \n",
    "    \"cadence_variability\",\n",
    "    \"sentence_entropy\",\n",
    "    \"metaphor_frequency\",\n",
    "    \"abstraction_level\",\n",
    "    \"assertiveness_score\",\n",
    "    \"rhythm_signature\",\n",
    "    \"narrative_intensity_curve\",\n",
    "    \"cognitive_load_index\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Resonance Dimensions ({len(RESONANCE_DIMENSIONS)}):\")\n",
    "for i, dim in enumerate(RESONANCE_DIMENSIONS, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i:2d}. {dim.replace('_', ' ').title()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2 Similarity Calculation\n",
    "\n",
    "The primary similarity metric is cosine similarity:\n",
    "\n",
    "$S_{cosine} = \\frac{R_{current} \\cdot R_{target}}{||R_{current}|| \\cdot ||R_{target}||}$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $R_{current}$ is the generated text resonance vector and $R_{target}$ is the target profile vector."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def cosine_similarity(vector1: np.ndarray, vector2: np.ndarray) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate cosine similarity between two vectors\"\"\"\n",
    "    dot_product = np.dot(vector1, vector2)\n",
    "    norm1 = np.linalg.norm(vector1)\n",
    "    norm2 = np.linalg.norm(vector2)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if norm1 == 0 or norm2 == 0:\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return dot_product / (norm1 * norm2)\n",
    "\n",
    "def euclidean_similarity(vector1: np.ndarray, vector2: np.ndarray) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate euclidean distance similarity\"\"\"\n",
    "    distance = np.linalg.norm(vector1 - vector2)\n",
    "    max_distance = np.sqrt(len(vector1))  # Maximum possible distance\n",
    "    return 1.0 - (distance / max_distance)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test similarity calculations\n",
    "test_vector1 = np.array([0.8, 0.6, 0.7, 0.5, 0.9, 0.4, 0.7, 0.6, 0.8, 0.5])\n",
    "test_vector2 = np.array([0.7, 0.7, 0.6, 0.6, 0.8, 0.5, 0.6, 0.7, 0.7, 0.6])\n",
    "\n",
    "cos_sim = cosine_similarity(test_vector1, test_vector2)\n",
    "euc_sim = euclidean_similarity(test_vector1, test_vector2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Cosine Similarity: {cos_sim:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Euclidean Similarity: {euc_sim:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.3 Drift Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Drift rate is calculated as the derivative of similarity over time:\n",
    "\n",
    "$D = \\frac{dS}{dt}$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $S$ is the similarity score and $t$ is time (or generation step)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_drift_rate(similarity_history: List[float]) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate drift rate from similarity history\"\"\"\n",
    "    if len(similarity_history) < 2:\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Use linear regression to estimate trend\n",
    "    x = np.arange(len(similarity_history))\n",
    "    y = np.array(similarity_history)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate slope (rate of change)\n",
    "    coeffs = np.polyfit(x, y, 1)\n",
    "    drift_rate = abs(coeffs[0])  # Absolute value for magnitude\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return drift_rate\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulate drift detection\n",
    "similarity_history = [0.95, 0.93, 0.91, 0.89, 0.87, 0.85, 0.83]\n",
    "drift = calculate_drift_rate(similarity_history)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Similarity history: {similarity_history}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Drift rate: {drift:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Drift severity: {'High' if drift > 0.02 else 'Medium' if drift > 0.01 else 'Low'}\")"
   ]
  },
